{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01T3osspVBTmJYigurmGJfTP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n\n1. The case should have set up:\n   - Two IngressClasses: `ingress-1` and `ingress-2`\n   - An `ingress-2.yaml` controller for handling `ingress-2` class\n   - An `ingress-gateway` ExternalName service pointing to the `ingress-nginx-2` namespace controller\n   - A `demo-app` Ingress with `class.example.com` but apparently without `ingressClassName` (or with `ingress-2`)\n\n2. The actual state of the cluster is missing:\n   - The IngressClasses and second controller in the `ingress-nginx-2` namespace\n   - The `ingress-gateway` service in the demo namespace\n\nThe scenario involves creating a new ingress for `class.example.com` that should use the `ingress-2` class, but the current demo-app ingress is configured with the default `nginx` class and handles `demo.example.com/app` instead. The preconditions weren't properly established to support this routing configuration.\n\nLet me look at the test.yaml to understand what the preconditions were actually supposed to set up.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":457,"cache_read_input_tokens":34227,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":457},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e023a6af-4311-4a8e-ae73-89b8025e767d","uuid":"3201474b-bc9b-4db4-8750-548b641743b1","request_id":"req_011Cc7mTXfZLAmgbBjfAUxGz"}
